obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (67109)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00068_198041_1658138840430&sectionId=67109&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00068_198041_1658138840430
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Essential Services Maintenance`
  line `(Assam) Act, 1980.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of the State of Assam.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (67110)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00068_198041_1658138840430&sectionId=67110&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00068_198041_1658138840430
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line ^1[***]
  line
  line `^2[(b) "essential service" means--`
  line
  line `(i) any transport services for the carriage of passengers or goods, by land or water with`
  line `respect to which the Legislative Assembly of the State of Assam has power to make laws;`
  line
  line `(ii) any service connected with the production, storage, supply or distribution, as the case may`
  line `be, of gas or water;`
  line
  line `(iii) any service connected with the maintenance of public health and sanitation, including`
  line `hospitals and dispensaries;`
  line
  line `(iv) any public services and posts in connection with the affairs of the State, and also persons`
  line `appointed to the secretarial staff of the Legislative Assembly of the State of Assam;`
  line
  line `(v) any other service or employment or class thereof, connected with matters with respect to`
  line `which the Legislative Assembly of the State of Assam has power to make laws and which the`
  line `State Government, being of opinion that strikes therein would prejudicially affect the`
  line `maintenance of any public utility service, the public safety or the maintenance of the supplies and`
  line `services necessary for the life of the community or would result in the infliction of grave hardship`
  line `on the community, may, by notification in the official gazette, declare to be an essential service`
  line `for the purpose of this Act;`
  line
  line `(bb) 'State Government' means the State Government of Assam;]`
  line
  line `(c) "strike" means the cessation of work by a body of persons employed in any essential service`
  line `acting in combination or a concerted refusal or a refusal under a common understanding of any`
  line `number of persons who are or who have been so employed to continue to work or to accept`
  line `employment, and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) refusal to work overtime where such work is necessary for the maintenance of any`
  line `essential service;`
  line
  line `(ii) any other conduct which is likely to result in, or results ill, cessation or substantial`
  line `retardation of work in any essential service.`
  line
  line `(2) Every notification issued ^3[under sub-clause (v)] of clause (6) of sub-section (1) shall be laid`
  line `before each House of Parliament immediately after it is made if it is in session and on the first day of the`
  line `commencement of the next session of the House if it is not in session, and shall cease to operate at the`
  line `expiration of forty days from the date of its being so laid or from the re-assembly of Parliament, as the`
  line `case may be, unless before the expiration of that period a resolution approving the issue of the notification`
  line `is passed by both Houses of Parliament.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- Where the Houses of Parliament are summoned to re- assemble on different dates, the`
  line `period of forty days shall be reckoned from the later of those dates.`
  line
  line `(3) Any reference in this Act to any law which is not in force in any area of the State of Assam and to`
  line `any authority under such law shall, in relation to that area, be construed as a reference to the`
  line `corresponding law in force in that area and to the corresponding authority under such corresponding law.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Omitted by Act, 40 of 1981, s. 13, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 26-7-1981).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 13, ibid, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 26-7-1981),`
  line
  line `* Act 40 of 1981 shall cease to have effect on the expiry of nine years from the date of assent to the Act 40 of 1981 i.e, (23-9-`
  line `1981).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 40 of 1981, s. 13, for "under sub-clause (xiv)" (w.e.f. 23-9-1981).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (67111)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power to prohibit strikes in certain employments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 13, ibid, for "appropriate Government" (w.e.f. 23-9-1981).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00068_198041_1658138840430&sectionId=67111&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00068_198041_1658138840430
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the ^1[State Government] is satisfied`
  line `that in the public interest it is necessary or expedient so to do, it may, by general or special Order, prohibit`
  line `strikes in the State of Assam in any essential service specified in the Order.`
  line
  line `(2) An Order made under sub-section (1) shall be published in such manner as the ^1[State`
  line `Government] considers best calculated to bring it to the notice of the persons affected by the Order.`
  line
  line `(3) An Order made under sub-section (1) shall be in force for six months only, but the ^1[State`
  line `Government] may, by a like Order, extend it for any period not exceeding six months if it is satisfied that`
  line `in the public interest it is necessary or expedient so to do.`
  line
  line `(4) Upon the issue of an Order under sub-section (1), --`
  line
  line `(a) no person employed in any essential service to which the Order relates shall go or remain on`
  line strike;
  line
  line `(b) any strike declared or commenced, whether before or after the issue of the Order, by persons`
  line `employed in any such service shall be illegal.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (67112)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Dismissal of employees participating in illegal strikes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00068_198041_1658138840430&sectionId=67112&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00068_198041_1658138840430
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Any person who commences a strike`
  line `which is illegal under this Act, or goes or remains on, or otherwise takes part in, any such strike, shall be`
  line `liable to disciplinary action (including dismissal) in accordance with the same pro-visions as are`
  line `applicable for the purpose of taking such disciplinary action (including dismissal) on any other ground`
  line `under the terms and conditions of service applicable to him in relation to his employment.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (67113)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Penalty for illegal strikes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00068_198041_1658138840430&sectionId=67113&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00068_198041_1658138840430
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Any person who commences a strike which is illegal under this Act,`
  line `or goes or remains on, or otherwise takes part in, any such strike shall be punishable with imprisonment`
  line `for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or`
  line `with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (67114)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Penalty for instigation, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00068_198041_1658138840430&sectionId=67114&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00068_198041_1658138840430
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Any person who instigates or incites other persons to take part in, or`
  line `otherwise acts in furtherance of, a strike which is illegal under this Act shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine which may extend to two thousand`
  line `rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (67115)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Penalty for giving financial aid to illegal strikes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00068_198041_1658138840430&sectionId=67115&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00068_198041_1658138840430
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Any person who knowingly expends or`
  line `supplies any money in furtherance or support of a strike which is illegal under this Act shall be punishable`
  line `with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine which may extend to two`
  line `thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (67116)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power to arrest without warrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00068_198041_1658138840430&sectionId=67116&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00068_198041_1658138840430
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), any police officer may arrest without warrant any person who is reasonably`
  line `suspected of having committed any offence under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (67117)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Offences to be tried summarily.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 40 of 1981, s. 13, for "appropriate Government" (w.e.f. 23-9-1981).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00068_198041_1658138840430&sectionId=67117&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00068_198041_1658138840430
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), all offences under this Act shall be tried in a summary way by a Judicial`
  line `Magistrate of the first class specially empowered in this behalf by the ^1[State Government] and the`
  line `provisions of Sections 262 to 265 (both inclusive) of the said Code shall, as far as may be, apply to such`
  line `trial:`
  line
  line `Provided that in a case of conviction for any offence in a summary trial under this section, it shall be`
  line `lawful for the Magistrate to pass a sentence of imprisonment for any term for which such offence is`
  line `punishable under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (67118)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Act to override other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00068_198041_1658138840430&sectionId=67118&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00068_198041_1658138840430
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act and of any Order issued there under`
  line `shall have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in the Industrial Disputes Act,`
  line `1947 (14 of 1947), or in any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (67119)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00068_198041_1658138840430&sectionId=67119&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00068_198041_1658138840430
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Essential Services Maintenance (Assam) Ordinance, 1980 (2 of`
  line `1980), is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the said Ordinance shall be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under this Act, as if this Act had come into force on the 6th day of`
  line `April, 1980.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
